    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If the proposed release is accepted, it leaves Waller the same rights and
                    remedies before French tribunals as would under like circumstances be available
                    to a foreigner.<note n="1" xml:id="d346fn1">Frenchman.</note> The foreign office
                    will then require an exchange of letters with this embassy that the incident is
                    closed between the two Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eustis</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
